title: Chief CJ3
description: I led an 82 man NATO Coalition team as Chief CJ3 (essentially OC Ops/Airfield Manager) to Commander, Kandahar Airfield (KAF) (COMKAF). With almost 400 aircraft permanently based there, KAF is the World's busiest single runway airfield, Afghanistan's busiest heliport and ISAF's principal strategic air base. These aircraft are a unique combination of military and civilian fixed wing (Fast jet CAS, C4ISR, transport, commercial and RPA/UAS) and rotary wing assets. During my tenure, operations reached unprecedented levels of 800 fixed wing sorties alone per day with fixed and rotary movements combining to produce over 40 000 per month (2012 saw 473 000 movements at KAF. In comparison, London Gatwick experienced 240 000 movements in 2011-12 with the luxury of an alternative runway). These record levels were achieved despite extensive essential repairs to taxiways and both thresholds of KAF's runway during my tour. I led Coalition military and contractor personnel in coordinating these contracts (worth approximately £20M) with operations to ensure that impact to ISAF capacity and Afghan commercial interests was minimised. This involved liaison with tenant NATO and Afghan military units, ISAF Joint Command, CAOC, contractors as well as the Afghan Ministry of Transport and Civil Aviation. Although CJ3 focused, I became heavily involved in advising IJC and NATO JFC Brunssum in transition planning, notably regarding future ISR posture, basing options and the transfer of KAF facilities to Afghan control. Aligned to this, I assisted in the mentoring of the Afghan Airport Manager of the civilian terminal to develop the nascent commercial potential of this facility. Other responsibilities involved the staffing of Coalition basing requests and the recovery of airfield operations following insurgent rocket and suicide attacks.

Key activities included coordination and operational level tasking of the following: Afghanistan. - Base ISTAR (notably CORTEZ and aerostats). - Force Protection/Counter Threat (including Unattended Ground Sensors and Counter Improvised Explosive Device). - UAS/RPAS capabilities and integration (H450, Watchkeeper, Desert Hawk 3, Predator and Reaper). - Air C2ISR (Nimrod R1, Sentinel R1, Sea King ASaC7, E-3D, GR4 RAPTOR/Litening III). - SF capabilities. - Operational trials. - Staffing of Urgent Operational Requirements (UOR).
